<br />
I cancelled my account a while ago. Just because I can't afford to be auto billed every 3 months when I don't have the money. 
<br />

<br />
all in all I find this to be rather silly. Keep in mind - 
<br />

<br />
SoE wrote: 
<br />
You're in our world now  
<br />

<br />

<br />
Enchanters were never intended to be an offensive class. We've always been needed in raid and group situations as support. I can honestly say I have never seen any one on the luclin server that has met my caliper of being able to control a charm pet in groups. 
<br />

<br />
And I know for a fact 99% of the enchanter that started taking up charming are the enchanters that read the guides on it that were printed out till after the release of PoP. 
<br />

<br />
We all did fine Pre PoP, and we've all been asking for EQ to go back to their roots. Now that they are, (Bards not being able to make Massive AA's, Warriors not being replaced by SK's and Pal's, and enchanters being made back into a support class) 
<br />

<br />
It was fun while it lasted, but every one is making a huge deal about something they said they have been working on since day one of the influx of chanter's using charm DPS. 
<br />

<br />
My game isn't ruined, I just found other things to do instead of looking for the easy way out. Gratz me on becoming a raid leader, and a class leader in my guild. 
<br />
 </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Back to basics?
<br />

<br />
I started back in April of '99 and am very close to quitting both EQ and EQII at this point (yes, I made it into beta when they first opened up the "special beta").  Why? Mostly because of the issue of Sony ignoring the needs of it's customers and not at least commenting on the needs thereof.  Back in the day, Enchanters had debuffs that were barely second to Shaman, we stacked well with them in fact.  We had buffs that were also quite nice, speed, rune and clarity first and foremost.  However, most of our other buffs were, and still are, useless.  How many times have you been asked for str?  How about your HP buff?  Shaman quickly outpaced our ability to debuff, and now Bards can rival our speed.  Druids always had the better Str buff and Clerics the HP buff... however, I could live with that as I had a necessary role in a group: CC.
<br />

<br />
With my speed, clarity and CC ability, I could help a group scream through content.  Icing on the cake was the ability to put up Boon of the Garou... note that NDT is now overshadowed by Avatar, most folks will only "suffer" NDT at this point and will drop it in a heartbeat for Avatar.
<br />

<br />
So, how are we going back to the "old school" here?  Our debuffs are tertiary to other classes.  Our buffs may rival but the fact that it's the ONLY thing we do means that we are not as desirable as other classes that can do nearly the same buffs, and in most cases CC as well, AND provide DPS or other buffs to the group.
<br />

<br />
This isn't back to old school... this is ripping the heart and soul out of the class.  If we are to be buff bots, give us some good buffs that rival other characters.  Make groups have to decide on an Enchanter on an equal footing with the other classes.  Don't relegate our buffs to something that can be purchased in PoK and then we are left to rot in that zone while the group goes and has fun... give the group incentive to add us as a valuable member to the group.
<br />

<br />
Right now I get groups... why?  Because I still pull and my wife and I arrange the groups from our guild/alliance... thus, I'm working with friends for group material, strictly.  I pull fast, and since I'm no DPS whatsoever, the DPS classes are allowed to do just that: provide DPS.[/quote]</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />GnarliAnna
<br />

<br />
Not flaming in a room of flammables is a nigh on impossible task!
<br />

