                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Oh puhlease
<br />

<br />
All these 'Oh, I was charming 100 years ago' posts are irrelevant and you know it. SoE fundamentally chamged the basic model they used to design mobs with PoP and that had a huge impact on charm. 
<br />

<br />
Before, charm was useful for soloing stuff (slowly) and as a CC measure in areas with mobs immune to mez. Using Boltrans for dps was a nice way to show-off, but largely inefficient unless your group was lacking.
<br />

<br />
With PoP things changed dramatically, and you all know it, because the basic nature of mobs changed. Personally, I thought the whining about the original state of PoP charm was ridiculous - so what if people could solo nameds or grind exp fast, that's been true for years if you were smart and not a melee. But it was clear that they were going to run into problems with scaling on this model. 
<br />

<br />
In GoD they ran into that problem when the first guilds got into kod'taz and started tearing through the stuff there. The fact that some Ikkinz trials were trivial with charm was a problem, but nerfing charm in Kod'taz itself was a bad decision as that zone became an important exp area for many. Taking charm away just to safeguard a raid event that most guilds would do once only was a spectacular mistake, but we need to be hitting them on the head for the mistakes they made, not giving them broad general accusations that they can simply shrug off because they're manifestly untrue.
<br />

<br />
Yeah, charm needed some adjustment with OoW, because they've pushed the high dps/low hp model up another notch and charm mob damage would just get out of control. As usual, they overnerfed to the extent that charm became pretty much worthless except in some cases. If you think the 50% damage reduction is bad, try charming a 1.6k hitter just to find it hitting for 215. But nonsense like 'this is ripping the heart and soul out of the class.' does nothing for the argument and just cheapens our case for improvements. I can still solo nameds for runes, I still spend a lot of time doing the same things I've been doing for years. Charmed-mob damage needs to be increased, especially for exp groups, but this isn't the big drama some people are trying to make of it.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
