                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ah, changes to charmed pets.
<br />
I also remember when the target bar only updated once a tick and you had to spam TAB to make it refresh.
<br />

<br />
How about being incapable of running faster than your target (no such thing as run speed), and having to hold down CTRL and strafe-run to get ahead?
<br />

<br />
There didn't used to be a green bar below your name to indicate an active pet.
<br />

<br />
If your pet got poisoned or diseased, it would continue to be angry at the monster and chase it back to whereever it gated to.
<br />

<br />
You could make pets break mez on command before.  Wish they hadn't changed that - pet control was one of the things that separated the incompetent pet classes from the skilled ones.  Now, if you want a pet that breaks mez on command, you need to pick up an undead one.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
